Last month, Foreign Secretary Liz Truss introduced the new legislation into the UK parliament that would see Britain override large parts of that agreement, although questions have been raised over its legality. In a fresh outburst, European Commission vice president Mr Sefcovic told the European Parliament in Strasbourg: "We need to be realistic - no alternative solution has been found and it is not needed. There is no legal or political justification whatsoever for the UK to unilaterally change an international agreement." FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...